      "content": "Interesting. The way they justify it as protecting \"community standards\" is a good touch for the realism. Please continue that last thought about the NAACP and the schools. I want to see them delve deeper into the specific reasons why they believe the existing social structure is necessary for the stability of the town and how they view the inevitable friction that comes from these changes.",
